    "VERSE": "38:84",
    "ARABIC": "\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0641\u064e\u0671\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0642\u0651\u064f \u0648\u064e\u0671\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0642\u0651\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0642\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f",
    "ENGLISH": {
        "TRANSLATION_0": "He said, 'By the truth - and I speak the truth -",
        "TRANSLATION_1": "(God) said: \"This is right by Me, and what I say is right.\n",
        "TRANSLATION_2": "He (i.e. Allah) said: \u201cThis is the Truth -- and I only speak the Truth --\n",
        "TRANSLATION_3": "The Lord said, \"I swear by the Truth - and I speak the Truth -\n",
        "TRANSLATION_4": "Said Allah, \u201cSo this is the truth; and I speak only the truth.\u201d \u2013\n",
        "TRANSLATION_5": "(Allah) said: \"The truth is -- the truth I say - \"\n",
        "TRANSLATION_6": "He said: The truth then is and the truth do I speak:\n",
        "TRANSLATION_7": "Said He, 'This is the truth, and the truth I say;\n",
        "TRANSLATION_8": "He said: The Truth is, and the Truth I speak,\n",
        "TRANSLATION_9": "God said, \"This is the truth, I speak only the truth,\n",
        "TRANSLATION_10": "Allah said: the truth is, and it is the truth that I speak, -\n",
        "TRANSLATION_11": "Said He, \u2018The truth is that\u2014and I speak the truth\u2014\n",
        "TRANSLATION_12": "(Allah) said: \"Then it is just and fitting- and I say what is just and fitting-\n",
        "TRANSLATION_13": "(Allah) said: \"The Truth is, and the Truth I say,\n",
        "TRANSLATION_14": "He (Allah) said: 'This is the truth, and I speak the truth:\n",
        "TRANSLATION_15": "He said, \u201cThe truth is, and I say the truth.\n",
        "TRANSLATION_16": "[Allah] said, \"The truth [is My oath], and the truth I say -\n",
        "TRANSLATION_17": "[38:84] He said, \u2018So the truth is \u2014 and the truth I [always] speak (read both [words] in the accusative [fa\u2019l-haqqa wa\u2019l-haqqa]; or with the first in the nominative and the second in the accusative because of the verb [aq\u016blu, \u2018I speak\u2019] that follows. As for reading the first one in the accusative, this would be on account of the mentioned verb [q\u0101la, \u2018he said\u2019]; but it is also said to be on account of its being a verbal noun, the sense being uhiqqu l-haqqa, \u2018I establish the truth\u2019; or [it is in the accusative by implication] if the particle for the oath [fa] is removed. It [the first haqq] could also be in the nominative because of its being the subject of a missing predicate, as in fa\u2019l-haqqu minn\u012b, \u2018truth [comes] from Me\u2019. It is also said that [the sentence means] fa\u2019l-haqqu qasam\u012b, \u2018the truth is [this] oath from Me\u2019, the response to which is the following [la-amla\u2019anna \u2026]) \u2014\n",
        "TRANSLATION_18": "(He said) Allah said to him: (The Truth is) I am the Truth, (and the Truth I speak,\n"
    },
